            <img src="C:\Users\khanm\OneDrive\Desktop\CodeSoft\Mahatma Gandhi.jpg" alt="Mahatma Gandhi">
            <h2>About Mahatma Gandhi</h2>
            <p>Mahatma Gandhi, born Mohandas Karamchand Gandhi, was a leader of the Indian independence movement against
                British rule. He is renowned for his philosophy of nonviolent resistance and his pivotal role in India's
                quest for freedom.</p>
            <p>Born on October 2, 1869, in Porbandar, India, Gandhi studied law in London before working in South
                Africa, where he developed his political and ethical views. Upon returning to India, he led nationwide
                campaigns for easing poverty, expanding women's rights, building religious and ethnic amity, ending
                untouchability, and, above all, achieving Swaraj or self-rule.</p>
            <p>Gandhi's vision and actions inspired movements for civil rights and freedom across the world. He was
                assassinated on January 30, 1948, but remains an enduring symbol of peace and nonviolent protest.</p>
        </section>
        <section id="timeline">
            <h2>Timeline of Major Events</h2>
            <div class="event">
                <h3>1869</h3>
                <p>Born in Porbandar, India</p>
            </div>
            <div class="event">
                <h3>1888</h3>
                <p>Traveled to London to study law</p>
            </div>
            <div class="event">
                <h3>1915</h3>
                <p>Returned to India and joined the Indian National Congress</p>
            </div>
            <div class="event">
                <h3>1930</h3>
                <p>Led the Salt March to protest the British salt tax</p>
            </div>
            <div class="event">
                <h3>1947</h3>
                <p>India gained independence from British rule</p>
            </div>
            <div class="event">
                <h3>1948</h3>
                <p>Assassinated in New Delhi, India</p>
